== Setting up on MacOS

MacOS is built on top of a Linux operating system, so installing things can be a bit smoother on MacOS than on windows. 



include::sections/working-with-the-trerminal.asc[]

include::sections/installers.asc[]

=== Turning your MacOS machine into a Linux machine

Well, your MacOS is built on Linux so it actually is already a Linux machine. However, if you want to have a full blown Linux operating system, you read the section on <<Creating a Linux environment inside any computer>>. 

=== Summary

By now you should be able to pull up a powershell and call the essential programs we will be working with in this course.
